        <SESSION ID='session_01'>
          <NAME>defaultSession</NAME>
          <NUMBER>0x01</NUMBER>
          <DESCRIPTION>This diagnostic session enables the default diagnostic session in the server(s) and does not support any diagnostic application timeout handling provisions (e.g., TesterPresent service is not necessary to keep the session active). A server shall always start the default diagnostic session when powered up. If no other diagnostic session is started, then the default diagnostic session shall be running as long as the server is powered. </DESCRIPTION>
          <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>Items used in session entry criteria:

(1) Automatically entered within 50 ms after ECU reset or ECU power up

(2) Receipt of diagnosticSessionControl with subfunction value of $01 (defaultSession)



Session Entry Criteria:  (1 or 2)</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
          <EXIT_CONDITIONS>Items used in session exit criteria:

(1)  Receipt of diagnosticSessionControl with an ECU supported subfunction value other than $01 (assuming all entry conditions are met for the requested session).

(2)  Power is removed from the ECU

Session Exit Criteria:  (1, 2)</EXIT_CONDITIONS>
        </SESSION>
        <SESSION ID='session_02'>
          <NAME>programmingSession</NAME>
          <NUMBER>0x02</NUMBER>
          <DESCRIPTION>This diagnosticSession enables all diagnostic services required to support the memory programming of a server.  Regardless of whether the programmingSession runs in boot software or not, the ECU shall automatically suspend logging of DTCs and suspend transmission of non-diagnostic frames when entering the programmingSession.



Note:  Download sequence should be initiated only 10 secs after tool is connected</DESCRIPTION>
          <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>Items used in session entry criteria:

      <DID ID='did_FD01'>
        <NAME>DRX Parameters</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0xFD01</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>Supplier usage only

Timer Parameters used in DRX mode

Byte 1  CONNECTION_EXTEND_MINUTES; maxuimum time TCU will stay in Full Power StandbyDRX stage;

Bytes 2-3  CONTINUOUS SCAN_PERIOD; maximum time TCU will stay in Low Power Registered DRX stage -- Obsolete in ECG2, moved to 0xDE0B for EOL configuration;

Byte 4  HI_RATE_DELAY; delay time between start of DRX wakeups in Hi Rate Scan DRX stage;

Byte 5 Hi_RATE_TOTAL_SCANS; maximum number of scans TCU will perform in Hi Rate Scan stage;

Byte 6  LO_RATE_DELAY; delay time between start of DRX wakeups in Lo Rate Scan DRX stage;

Byte 7  LO_RATE_TOTAL_SCANS; maximum number of scans TCU will perform in Lo Rate Scan stage;

Byte 8  DRX_WAKEUP; Minimum time TCU will scan for network messages during a DRX wakeup;



With the default parameters shown, an uninterrupted DRX cycle runs as follows:

 Full Power Standby for 30 minutes,

 Hi Rate Scan starts a DRX wakeup once every 4 hours, but is disabled,

 Low Rate Scan starts a DRX wakeup once every 8 hours, but is disabled.

      <DID ID='did_DE12'>
        <NAME>DepletBattTempLevel</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0xDE12</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>Config Type  = Type 5

Apply Type = Immediate



This group of data indicates the maximum SoC depletion for each feature severity level, battery type and battery temperature. Batt1 = the battery type of Undefined OR Flooded OR Flooded Sealed. Batt2 = the battery type of Improved Flooded OR Improved Flooded Sealed. Batt3 = the battery type of AGM. In order to be granted permission, a request with a specific severity level must meet two conditions: it's MinSoc value must be greater than current SOC value AND the SOC value when ignition off minus it's depletion value must be greater than current SOC value.</DESCRIPTION>

        <NAME>MinSocBattTempLevel</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0xDE15</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>Config Type  = Type 5

Apply Type = Immediate



This group of data indicates the minimum SoC for each feature severity level, battery type and battery temperature. Batt1 = the battery type of Undefined OR Flooded OR Flooded Sealed.       <ROUTINE ID='routine_0218' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03'>
        <NAME>Cancel OTA Update</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x0218</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>The purpose of this Routine is to cancel an active OTA update (triggered) that is not yet progress.  Not in progress means it has not yet been activated on any ECU or has begun a SWDL update of any ECU.

Note: time duration before running the routine is defined in &quot;Special Procedure - Maximum Duration to start Type 2 routine tests&quot;.</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>60000</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>The routine shall enter test only if all the

following criteria are met (if not correct: send conditions not

correct message to tester):

1) Ignition is in the Run or Accessory State or Crank State (DID 0x411F)

2) Battery Voltage is Between 9-17 volts (DID 0xD111)

3) Extended Diagnostic Session (DID 0xD100)</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>The routine shall exit test if any one of the

following criteria is met:

1)Ignition transitions out of Run or Accessory State or Crank State (DID 0x411F)

2)Battery Voltage Drops below 9 volts or exceeds 17 volts (DID 0xD111)

3)Test is complete.</EXIT_CONDITIONS>

        <DESCRIPTION>This routine control is the trigger to initiate the manual unlocking mechanism to access: 1. From Gateway Network Protection (GNP) Mode 1: Unlock  to Gateway Network Protection (GNP) Mode 4: Factory Pass Data  (or) 2. From Gateway Network Protection Mode (GNP) 4: Factory Pass Data to Gateway Network Protection (GNP) Mode 1:  Unlock -&gt; extracted from VSEM

correct message to tester):

1) GNP Unlocking Procedure is executed successfully</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>GNP Unlock/Lock Gateway Network Protection (GNP) (7012) shall exit self-test if any one of the following criteria is met:

1)GNP Locking Procedure is executed successfully  

2)GNP Mode 4: Factory Pass Data counter times out</EXIT_CONDITIONS>

      <ROUTINE ID='routine_7014' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03' SECURITY_REFS='security_level_2'>
        <NAME>CAN Message Authentication Key Management Operation</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x7014</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>This routine triggers the ECG to initiate the key management operation. ECG up on receiving this routine control request, checks the Action Identifier (AID) that is contained in the first two bytes of the routine control option record and performs the actions specific to the AID.



Note: The size of Request Data/Sequence is range from 272 bytes to 4080 bytes.

Note: time duration before running the routine is defined in &quot;Special Procedure - Maximum Duration to start Type 2 routine tests&quot;.

</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>180000</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>CAN Message Authentication key Management Operation (7014) shall start only if all the

following criteria are met (if not correct: send conditions not

correct message to tester):

1) Ignition is in the Run state (DID 0x411F)

2) Extended Diagnostic Session (DID 0xD100)

3) Security Access Level 0x03 

4) Vehicle speed is less than 5 KPH

5) CAN Message Authentication key Management Operation (7014) is requested by tester via start routine subfunction</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>CAN Message Authentication key Management Operation (7014) shall exit if any one of the

following criteria is met:

1)Ignition transitions out of Run state

2)A stop routine command is issued.

3)Tester does not communicate for more than five (5) seconds.

4) Vehicle speed goes above 5 KPH

5) Routine Execution is complete.</EXIT_CONDITIONS>
        <ROUTINE_START_PARAMETERS>
          <ROUTINE_REQUEST_PARAMETERS>
            <ROUTINE_PARAM>
              <NAME>Request Additional Data</NAME>
              <BYTE_SIZE>17</BYTE_SIZE>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_7014_subfield_1'>
                <NAME>Action Identifier</NAME>
                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>120</LEAST_SIG_BIT>
                <MOST_SIG_BIT>135</MOST_SIG_BIT>
                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>enumerated</DATA_TYPE>
                  <ENUMERATED_PARAMETERS>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x00</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Request Key Update at End of Line using Wildcard Authorization</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x01</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Dekey Entire Vehicle Using Wildcard Authorization</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x04</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Update Command Control Counter To Block Wildcard Commands</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x0101</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Command Gateway To Dekey A Module</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x0102</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Use Master Key Command To Dekey A Module</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x0103</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Use Master Key Command To Rekey A Module</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                    <ENUM_MEMBER>
                      <ENUM_VALUE>0x0105</ENUM_VALUE>
                      <DESCRIPTION>Restore The Encrypted Key Table On Gateway Module</DESCRIPTION>
                    </ENUM_MEMBER>
                  </ENUMERATED_PARAMETERS>
                </DATA_DEFINITION>
              </SUB_FIELD>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_7014_subfield_2'>
                <NAME>Command Control Counter</NAME>
                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>88</LEAST_SIG_BIT>
                <MOST_SIG_BIT>119</MOST_SIG_BIT>
                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>unsigned</DATA_TYPE>
                  <NUMERIC_PARAMETERS>
                    <RESOLUTION numerator='1' denominator='1'/>
                    <OFFSET>0</OFFSET>
                    <UNITS>Count</UNITS>
                  </NUMERIC_PARAMETERS>
                </DATA_DEFINITION>
              </SUB_FIELD>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_7014_subfield_3'>
                <NAME>Target Module On-Vehicle Telematics Protocol Identifier</NAME>
                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>72</LEAST_SIG_BIT>
                <MOST_SIG_BIT>87</MOST_SIG_BIT>
                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>bytes</DATA_TYPE>
                </DATA_DEFINITION>
              </SUB_FIELD>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_7014_subfield_4'>
                <NAME>Ford Electronic Serial Number Of The Gateway Module</NAME>
                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>8</LEAST_SIG_BIT>
                <MOST_SIG_BIT>71</MOST_SIG_BIT>
                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>ascii</DATA_TYPE>
                  <ASCII_PARAMETERS>
                    <JUSTIFICATION>left</JUSTIFICATION>
                    <ASCII_FILL_VALUE>0x00</ASCII_FILL_VALUE>
                  </ASCII_PARAMETERS>
                </DATA_DEFINITION>
              </SUB_FIELD>
              <SEQUENCE_OF>
                <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_7014_subfield_5'>
                  <NAME>Authorization Signature</NAME>
                  <LEAST_SIG_BIT>0</LEAST_SIG_BIT>

      <ROUTINE ID='routine_7015' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03' SECURITY_REFS='security_level_2'>
        <NAME>Initiate Trusted Realtime Operational Network Key Update</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x7015</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>This routine triggers the ECG to initiate the key distribution operation. ECG up on receiving this routine control request, checks the Action Identifier (AID) that is contained in the first two bytes of the routine control option record and performs the actions specific to the AID.



Note: The size of Request Data/Sequence is 272 bytes, and the size of Result Response Data/Sequence is range from 43 bytes to 4080 bytes.

Note: time duration before running the routine is defined in &quot;Special Procedure - Maximum Duration to start Type 2 routine tests&quot;.</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>180000</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>Initiate Trusted Realtime Operational Network Key Update (7015) shall start only if all the

following criteria are met (if not correct: send conditions not

correct message to tester):

1) Ignition is in the Run state(DID 0x411F)

2) Extended Diagnostic Session (DID 0xD100)

3) Security Access Level 0x03

4) Vehicle speed is less than 5 KPH

5) Initiate Trusted Realtime Operational Network Key Update (7015) is requested by tester via start routine subfunction</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>Initiate Trusted Realtime Operational Network Key Update (7015) shall exit if any one of the

following criteria is met:

1)Ignition transitions out of Run state(DID 0x411F)

2)A stop routine command is issued.

3)Tester does not communicate for more than five (5) seconds.

4) Vehicle speed goes above 5 KPH

5) Routine Execution is complete.</EXIT_CONDITIONS>

        <NAME>Request CAN Message Authentication Configurations</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x7016</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>This routine triggers the ECG to provide the current key injection status related to CMA keys. ECG up on receiving this routine control request, checks the Action Identifier (AID) that is contained in the first two bytes of the routine control option record and performs the actions specific to the AID.



Note: The size of Result Response Data/Sequence is range from 43 bytes to 4080 bytes.

      <ROUTINE ID='routine_800B' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03'>
        <NAME>Data File Retrieval</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x800B</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>Initial Application: Retrieve unsent data for China xEV Remote Data Monitoring requirements. steps: 1. Start the routine in the extednedDiagnosticSession - ECG responds with empty positive response.  2. Request routine results  - ECG responds with oldest file: raw data file (byte array with variable size 1 to n bytes). Max file size will be less than 4K. {0x00} will be returned if there are no more files to be retrieved. ECG deletes sent file after this request.  3. Repeats steps 1 and 2 until all the files are read

Note: time duration before running the routine is defined in &quot;Special Procedure - Maximum Duration to start Type 2 routine tests&quot;.</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>10000</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>The Data File Retrieval Routine (800B) shall enter operation only if all the following criteria are met

(if not correct: send conditions not correct message to tester):

1) China Data Monitor feature enabled (DID 0xDE01 Byte 1 Bit 2);

2) Ignition is in the Run or Accessory State or Crank State (DID 0x411F);

3) Battery Voltage is Between 9-17 volts (DID 0xD111);

4) Extended Diagnostic Session (DID 0xD100);

5) XXXXXX is requested by tester.</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>The Data File Retrieval Routine (800B) shall exit if any one of the following criteria is met:

1) Ignition transitions out of Run or Accessory State or Crank State (DID 0x411F)

2) Battery Voltage Drops below 9 volts or exceeds 17 volts (DID 0xD111)

3) A stop routine command is issued.

4) Tester does not communicate for more than five (5) seconds.

5) Test is complete.</EXIT_CONDITIONS>
        <ROUTINE_START_PARAMETERS>
          <ROUTINE_RESPONSE_PARAMETERS>
            <ROUTINE_PARAM>
              <NAME>RoutineInfo</NAME>
              <BYTE_SIZE>1</BYTE_SIZE>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_800B_subfield_1'>
                <NAME>RoutineType</NAME>
                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>4</LEAST_SIG_BIT>
                <MOST_SIG_BIT>7</MOST_SIG_BIT>
                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>enumerated</DATA_TYPE>

    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>EOL DID Collection &amp; Compare</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>List of DIDs for EOL by ECU:



ECUID = ECG:

1) Authorization State: DID 0xD021, ALL byte(s)  

2) Provisioning Method: DID 0xFD08, Byte 1 Bit 0  

3) CCS bPAllow_META: DID 0 x DE19 Byte 4, Bit 1 

4) Provisioning Uniform Resource Locator (URL): DID 0xD01E, ALL Byte(s

5) ECU_Provisioning_State: DID 0xFD02  ALL Bytes



ECUID = TCU:

6) Authorization State: DID 0xD021, ALL byte(s)  

7) Telematics SIM-Card ICC Number: DID 0x41AE, ALL Byte(s)  

8) WiFi Chipset MAC Address: DID 0xFD26, ALL byte(s) 

9) Cellular Radio Status: DID 0xCF04, ALL Byte(s)  

10) Access Point Name (APN): DID 0xD01D, ALL Byte(s) 

11) Embedded Universal Integrated Circuit Card ID: DID 0x6034, ALL Byte(s)



Each Ford Motor Company Assembly plant shall perform the following at each end of line for the above mentioned DIDs:



Read at Static , Gate Code Check or Equivalent:  

Always read DIDs 1, 2, 3, 4 ,5, 6 ,7 and 11

If DIDs 1 or 2 or 3 or 6 fail on comparison, also read:  8, 9 



Compare at Static/Equivalent and Gate Code Check:  

Always compare DIDs 1, 2, 3  

a) DID 1 fails if ECG  returns a value equal to (0x20) , DID 6 fails if TCU returns a value equal to (0x30)

b) DID 2 fails if ECG returns a value other than Cellular (0x0). If DID 2 returns  a value equal to (0x1) -configured to WIFI ,DID 2 shall be written to equal Cellular (0x0) at Static or Static Equivalent or Gate Code Check.

c) DID 3 ,fail if  Byte 4, Bit 1, “bPAllow_META3_Authorized” is enabled,plant shall perform a  ECG Master Reset via SYNC.

     -- If fails, perform master reset in the vehicle HMI settings. Go to SYNC settings -&gt; General -&gt; Master Reset -&gt; Continue

     -- If fails, alternative method to de-authorize the vehicle is to remove the VIN in FordPass app.  Open FordPass -&gt; Select the VIN -&gt; Go to Vehicle details -&gt; Remove VIN..



***Plant shall NOT allow vehicle to ship until the issue in item a), b) and c) has been resolved.***



Upload to GIVIS:

DID 7 and DID 11 shall always be uploaded to GIVIS @ Gate Code Check</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>

    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Maximum Duration to Start Type 2 Routine Tests</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>The ECG must be powered and active (awake) for at least 30 seconds before running the test for below Type 2 routines in order for the test to complete. If the test is started prior to this time period after power-on or reset, the VMCU might respond with NRC 0x21 (busyRepeatRequest) until ECG fully bootup.

Routine 0x0202 - On-Demand Self-Test

Routine 0x0218 - Cancel OTA Update

Routine 0x7012 - Unlock/Lock Gateway Network Protection (GNP)

Routine 0x7014 - CAN Message Authentication Key Management Operation

Routine 0x7015 - Initiate Trusted Realtime Operational Network Key Update

Routine 0x7016 - Request CAN Message Authentication Configurations

Routine 0x7017 - Request CAN Message Authentication Key Injection Status

Routine 0x800B - Data File Retrieval

Routine 0x800C - Vehicle Function Limiter Deinhibit

</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>
    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>

      <DESCRIPTION>End of Line should capture the following DIDs and upload to GiVIS:

0xF17F: FESN

0x8068: CCPU Boot Image

0x8033: Consumer Image Part Number

0x8060: Embedded Consumer Applications Part Numbers 1

0x8061: Embedded Consumer Applications Part Numbers 2

0x806A: Embedded Consumer Applications Part Numbers 3

0x806B: Embedded Consumer Applications Part Numbers 4

0x9140: Connected Blue Zone Map Data</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>
    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Maximum Duration to Start Type 1 Routine Tests</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>The ECG must be powered and active (awake) for at least 30 seconds before running the test for below Type 1 routines in order for the test to complete. If the test is started prior to this time period after power-on or reset, the VMCU might respond with NRC 0x10  (generalReject) and the test will fail.

Routine 0xDC00 - Erase All Debug Tokens

Routine 0xFF00 - Flash Erase









</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>
    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Adding Delay Between Module Reset and DID Read at EOL</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>After ECG “Reset” , ECG CP/VMCU takes ~125ms to boot up whereas ECG AP/CCPU takes &gt; 15 sec . After the module bootup, DID synchronization takes place between AP-CP processors. It is recommended to add a delay of &gt;15s between module reset and DID reads to complete the module boot up and error recovery routines. EOL team need to consider the ECG boot up time requirements</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>

    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Gateway Network Protection (GNP) Unlocking Procedure</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>GNP Mode 4 - Factory Pass Data:

To enter this State 4: GNP Modem 4 - Factory Pass Data:

1) Put the Gateway in Service 0x10 (0x03 extendedDiagnosticSession).

2) Security access service 0x27 Level 0x03 on gateway module is unlocked.

3) Execute Service 0x31 (Routine Control) on routine 0x7012 Unlock/Lock Gateway Network Protection (GNP).

4) Then the hazard light signal transitions from OFF to ON state and ON to OFF state within 20 seconds.

5) The Gateway module should now be unlocked, read DID 0xC015 to confirm GNP Mode 4: Factory Pass Data.</DESCRIPTION>

    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician end_of_line feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Message Authentication Service Routines at EOL part 2: Executing Routine 0x7016 with AID 0x0200</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>Executing Routine 0x7016 with AID 0x0200. To be executed at the end of EOL (i.e.: GCC)



Trigger routine 07016 with updated parameters, this AID is used to trigger the KeyM Client module to report out the current TRON configuration and provide as a routine control response. This allows TRON configuration to be stored in the backend for future repair purposes at FCSD. Routine has a maximum time defined for about 60 seconds



Request parameters to be used for the special procedure. Ignition must be ON for entire duration.

1. Parameter 1 shall be set to 0x0200



Note: GGMT reflash may occur at EOL or in service after successful key distribution has already occurred. GGMT reflash can result in erasure of the TRON Configuration, which would cause failure of AID 0x0200. Function Status 0x29 &quot;TRONConfigVINMismatch&quot; is provided as the status code for this scenario. CMA system recovery/repair at service is still possible even if the TRON Configuration for the given vehicle is not available. Since reporting of the TRON Configuration is not mission critical to service/repair purposes, this negative response may be ignored if experienced in manufacturing.</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>
    <PROCEDURE AUDIENCE='technician feedback development supplier'>
      <NAME>Special Procedures for Routine 0x800C Vehicle Function Limiter Deinhibit</NAME>
      <DESCRIPTION>Run the 0x800c routine using FDRS if DTC 0xD04000 is active, and this is only intended for service and not EOL.

1. Set the diagnostic session as &quot;extended Diagnostic Session&quot;

2. Verify battery voltage is between 9-17 volts

3. Set Ignition to on position

4. Establish security with module

5. Read VIN from vehicle

6. Read FESN from ECG module (DID 0xF17F)

7. Send VIN, FESN and vehicle payload to FDSP

     - FDSP sends VIN to GVMS to verify it is deinhibitable

     - If yes, FDSP sends VIN, FESN and vehicle payload to IVSS for SYNC-P Encryption

     - Payload returned to FDRS

8. Using FDRS send the following data to ECG module to De-inhibit vehicle

    - 0716 31 01 800c “Payload Data from IVSS”



</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>

      <DESCRIPTION>After the routine has been run, the expected Service Mode status can be verified by reading DID A021 &quot;Service Mode Status&quot; on ECG.</DESCRIPTION>
    </PROCEDURE>
